# Project rules (entry)

Use **`@`-references** instead of pasting long excerpts. Modular sources:

| Concern | Open |
|--------|------|
| Frozen UI / API vs safe refactors | `@.ai/core/refactor-policy.md` |
| Engineering habits | `@.ai/core/rules.md` |
| Product + sidebar + stack | `@.ai/projects/merchant-dashboard.md` |
| Visual system summary | `@design-guidelines/OVERVIEW.md` |
| Spec index (`rules/**/*.mdc`) | `@design-guidelines/INDEX.md` |
| Pack handoff / new repo | `@design-guidelines/README.md` |
| Module patterns (Agent Skill) | `@.cursor/skills/build-dashboard-module/SKILL.md` |
| Subagents (delegated specialists) | `.cursor/agents/*.md` ā€” index `@.cursor/agents/README.md`, reference `@.cursor/docs/subagents.md` |
| Prompts | `@.ai/prompts/safe-restructure.md`, `@.ai/prompts/concept-guidelines.md` |

**Guards:** Instruction-only work ā†’ do **not** edit `src/`. Granular design rules do **not** override `@.ai/core/refactor-policy.md`.

**Scoped UI rule:** `.cursor/rules/design-guidelines.mdc` (applies when `src/app` or `design-guidelines` files are in context).

## On every implementation or update

Do **not** rely on memory alone for tokens, layout, or refactor boundaries ā€” **open the relevant `@` files below** early so the first pass matches repo conventions and design.

1. **Scope and safety** ā€” If the change could affect layout, visuals, responsiveness, interactions, domain rules, or API usage, read **`@.ai/core/refactor-policy.md`** and stay within allowed lanes (or confirm wider scope before editing).
2. **Product and stack** ā€” For routes, merchant modules, or dashboard behaviour, read **`@.ai/projects/merchant-dashboard.md`**.
3. **Design consistency** ā€” For any work under `src/app/**` or `design-guidelines/**`, read **`@design-guidelines/OVERVIEW.md`** and **`@design-guidelines/INDEX.md`**, then the specific `design-guidelines/rules/**/*.mdc` specs the INDEX indicates for that surface. Reuse existing patterns, components, and tokens instead of inventing ad hoc styles.
4. **Engineering habits** ā€” Follow **`@.ai/core/rules.md`** (thin routes, no drive-by edits, incremental steps).
5. **Dashboard modules / sidebar** ā€” When the work matches that shape, follow **`@.cursor/skills/build-dashboard-module/SKILL.md`**.
6. **Implementation depth** ā€” Root **`.cursorrules`** defaults to complete, robust code; do not use that to override refactor-policy when the task is behaviour-preserving.

Rule types, globs, and `AGENTS.md`: [cursor.com/docs/rules](https://cursor.com/docs/rules). **Agent Skills** (this repo: `.cursor/skills/`): [cursor.com/docs/skills](https://cursor.com/docs/skills). **Subagents** (this repo: `.cursor/agents/`): [cursor.com/docs/subagents](https://cursor.com/docs/subagents).
